|CKBConcoct: Season to Taste, Disclose Nothing|000

Syntax: concoct <red salt|blue mixer|cutting bitters>
Alias:  cmix

At Rank 2 and Volatility 2, prepare one additive that lasts thirty minutes.
Use 'mix <additive> into <carried food or drink>'. One packet treats an entire
snack, meal, jug, or keg, provided the fare is not above the maker's level.

  Red restorative salt
    Alchemy 75; four red ash. Improves health recovery and adds brief health
    regeneration, but collects spell points at the door.

  Effervescent blue mixer
    Alchemy 75; four blue ash. Improves spell-point recovery and adds brief
    spell-point regeneration, but takes a small bite out of the customer.

  Cutting bitters
    Herbalism 50; three grey ash. Improves both kinds of healing and makes the
    meal easier to stomach, but briefly ruins concentration.

Higher Alchemy helps the red and blue mixtures, within reason. The packet is
transferable; the warranty is not. Inspect treated fare for exact values.
When consumed, it tells the customer how strong the lingering recovery is and
how long it will last. A humble meal does not secretly water down the dose.
